---
title: Chicken and Pineapple Quesadillas with Sweet Peppers, Caramelized Onion, and Pico de Gallo
description: If you thought sweet-and-savory combos were delicious, prepare to be blown away by this creamy cheese and pineapple dream-come-true. Although we recommend using only one chicken breast for the filling, feel free to use both for a super stuffed quesadilla.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chicken-and-pineapple-quesadilla-bed599c4.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-and-pineapple-quesadilla-af6a9e62.pdf
cuisine: Mexican
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-and-pineapple-quesadillas-57d85305518c880d0e8b4568
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 546 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 668 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1%unit}. Mince a few onion slices (you'll want about 2 Tablespoons) for the pico de gallo. Set aside in a #small bowl{}. Core, seed, and thinly slice the @Green Bell Pepper{1%unit}. Drain the @Pineapple{4%ounce}. Cut 1 @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. (Keep the other for a later use.)

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the sliced red onions and bell peppers. Cook, tossing occasionally, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Season with @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Chop the @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve the @Lime{1%unit}. Add the tomatoes and half the cilantro to the #bowl{} with the minced red onions. Stir in a squeeze of lime, and season with salt and pepper.

Cook the pineapple and chicken: Add the pineapple to the pan with the peppers and onions. Cook ~{2-3%minutes}, until slightly caramelized. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from the pan and set aside. Add the chicken, a drizzle of olive oil, and the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} to the pan. Cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until cooked through. Season with salt and pepper. Return the pineapple mixture to the pan along with a squeeze of lime and the remaining cilantro.

Using 2 @Whole Wheat Tortillas{4%unit} (we sent more), rub one side of each with a small drizzle of olive oil. Place oil-side down on a #baking sheet{}. Spread half the @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/2%cup} evenly onto each tortilla. Top with the chicken mixture and remaining cheese. Fold the tortillas over. Place under the broiler for ~{1-2%minutes}, until golden brown. Flip and broil ~{1-2%minutes} on the other side.

> Watch carefully so they don't burn!

Serve: Cut the chicken and pineapple quesadillas into wedges, and serve with the pico de gallo and @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}. Enjoy!